--------------------------
Steps for Installation
--------------------------
Manual Installation
PHP
Mysql
Netdata
S3cmd - for backup only

PRE SETUP
--------------------------
- stop cron job - comment out cron job entry.
- set .my.cnf with correct user name and password
- set config.sh file env settings
- EXECUTE generate_fresh_db_setup_script.sh - load the sql file for new and existing setup from staging db.
- Prepare update.sql/rollback.sql file for later update/rollback.

HOSTED FIRST TIME
--------------------------
** EXECUTE generate_fresh_db_setup_script.sh [Optional] - no need to run on RMLinux Server if .sql file is already generated
** Execute first_time_update.sh  - for first time update existing env

DEDICATED FIRST TIME
--------------------------
** EXECUTE generate_fresh_db_setup_script.sh [Optional] - no need to run on RMLinux Server if .sql file is already generated
** Execute first_time_update.sh   - for first time update existing env

HOSTED NEW ENV
--------------------------
** EXECUTE generate_fresh_db_setup_script.sh [Optional] - no need to run on RMLinux Server if .sql file is already generated
** Execute fresh_deployment.sh  - for first time update existing env

DEDICATED NEW ENV
--------------------------
** EXECUTE generate_fresh_db_setup_script.sh [Optional] - no need to run on RMLinux Server if .sql file is already generated
** Execute fresh_deployment.sh   - for first time update existing env
